explanations.description: Indefinite articles ("a", "an") and other determiners ("no", "some", "the") used to introduce a noun or noun phrase, and verbs ("give", "provide", "get", "become") that are part of idiomatic expressions or phrases that offer, convey, or receive something, especially information or assistance.
